SIMPLE: forerun
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Forerun
<hw>Fore*run"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To
turn before; to precede; to be in advance of (something
following).</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To come before as an earnest of something to follow;
to introduce as a harbinger; to announce.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>These signs <qex>forerun</qex> the death or fall of kings.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Forerunner</ent>⟦br⟧
